.TH "reset_buffer_flags" 9 "reset_buffer_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
reset_buffer_flags \- reset buffer state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" reset_buffer_flags
.BI "(struct n_tty_data *ldata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ldata" 12
line disc data to reset

Reset the read buffer counters and clear the flags.
Called from \fBn_tty_open\fP and \fBn_tty_flush_buffer\fP.

Locking: caller holds exclusive termios_rwsem
(or locking is not required)
